Evidence below is from commit `1c8023c7`. 1. AC1 — PASS. Evidence: [fugue-lane-bridge.mjs](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/fugue-lane-bridge.mjs), lines 360-365. Snippet: `if (provider === "codex" || provider === "codex-spark") { args.push("--project", project, "--auto-context"); if (delegationContextFile) { args.push("--delegation-context-file", delegationContextFile); } }` Note: ACPX providers bypass this block at lines 328-346, which matches the spec’s out-of-scope note. 2. AC2 — PASS. Evidence: [fugue-lane-bridge.mjs](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/fugue-lane-bridge.mjs), lines 296-323. Snippet: `const filePath = path.join(DELEGATION_CONTEXT_DIR, \`${runId}--${safeAgent}.md\`);` and `while (taskSummary && Buffer.byteLength(content, "utf8") > maxBytes) { ... }` and `const tempPath = \`${filePath}.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}.tmp\`;` Note: filename uses sanitized `safeAgent`; for current agent names that still yields the expected `{runId}--{agent}.md` shape. 3. AC3 — PASS. Evidence: [delegate.js](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/delegate.js), lines 212-214 and 388-404. Snippet: `} else if (args[i] === '--delegation-context-file' && args[i + 1]) { delegationContextFile = args[++i]; }` and `const contextFile = delegationContextFile || DEFAULT_DELEGATION_CONTEXT_FILE;` Note: this is a real read path, not just flag parsing. 4. AC4 — PASS. Evidence: [delegate.js](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/delegate.js), lines 398-401. Snippet: `const contextRunId = runIdMatch?.[1]?.trim(); if (ctx && (!runId || !contextRunId || contextRunId === runId)) { sections.push(...) }` Note: mismatched `run_id` is silently ignored; files with no parsable `run_id` are still accepted. 5. AC5 — PARTIAL. Evidence: [fugue-lane-bridge.mjs](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/fugue-lane-bridge.mjs), lines 292-293; [fugue-lane-bridge.mjs](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/fugue-lane-bridge.mjs), line 354; [delegate.js](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/delegate.js), line 434. Snippet: `const sanitizedTask = redactSecrets(String(task || "")).text.trim();` but later `const args = [scriptPath, "-a", agent, "-t", task, "--run-id", runId];` and `let fullPrompt = \`${agentPrompt}

## タスク
${task}\`;` Note: task text is redacted before writing the delegation context file, but raw `task` is still used as a CLI arg and in the prompt. 6. AC6 — PASS. Evidence: [fugue-lane-bridge.mjs](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/fugue-lane-bridge.mjs), lines 296-323 and 748-756; [output-format.js](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/lib/output-format.js), lines 56-58. Snippet: `const tempPath = \`${filePath}.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}.tmp\`;` and `const runId = generateRunId();` and `const settled = await Promise.allSettled(...)` Note: matrix lanes run in parallel, but each lane gets its own UUID runId and its own `{runId}--{agent}.md` path before atomic rename. 7. AC7 — PASS. Evidence: [delegate.js](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/delegate.js), lines 192, 388-393, 396-404. Snippet: `let delegationContextFile = '';` and `const contextFile = delegationContextFile || DEFAULT_DELEGATION_CONTEXT_FILE;` Note: missing flag falls back cleanly to the legacy fixed path. 8. AC8 — PASS. Evidence: [fugue-lane-bridge.mjs](/Users/masayuki/Dev/claude-config/assets/skills/orchestra-delegator/scripts/fugue-lane-bridge.mjs), lines 356-365. Snippet: `if ((provider === "glm" || provider === "gemini") ... ) { args.push("--context-files", ...) }` followed by a separate `if (provider === "codex" || provider === "codex-spark") { ... "--auto-context" ... }` Note: `grok` also has no ma...
